&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=" font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

    &lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0; padding-right: 12px;  padding-left: 12px;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;JavaScript Weekly&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181088/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/w_1280,e_sharpen:60,q_auto/jceavinnztxzgohscekg.jpg" width="640" style="    line-height: 100%;       "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181088/rss" title="oxc.rs" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.4em;"&gt;Oxfmt Beta: A Fast, Rust-Powered JavaScript Code Formatter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A &lt;strong&gt;100% &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181089/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Prettier&lt;/a&gt;-compatible&lt;/strong&gt; JavaScript code formatter (and sister project of &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181090/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Oxlint&lt;/a&gt;) that boasts being 30x faster than Prettier and 3x faster than &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181091/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Biome.&lt;/a&gt; Since the alpha, it now supports embedded language formatting (JSX, YAML, HTML, etc), Tailwind CSS &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181093/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;class sorting&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181094/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;import sorting&lt;/a&gt;, and¬†more.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Boshen, Dunqing, and Sugiura (VoidZero) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181087/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/c_limit,w_480,h_480,q_auto/copm/1cb4f684.png" width="148" height="110" style="padding-top: 12px; padding-left: 12px;     line-height: 100%;    "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181087/rss" title="developer.mescius.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;FlexGrid by Wijmo: The Industry-Leading JavaScript Datagrid&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A fast and flexible DataGrid for building modern web apps. Key features and virtualized rendering are included in the core grid module. Pick &amp;amp; choose special features to keep your app small. Built for JavaScript, extended to Angular, React, and¬†Vue.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Wijmo From MESCIUS &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #993 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN BRIEF:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Martin Kleppe, known for his creative experiments like &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181095/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;tixy.land&lt;/a&gt;, has created a &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181096/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;scrolling bitmap quine&lt;/a&gt; in just 666 characters of HTML and JavaScript. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181097/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Here's the annotated source&lt;/a&gt; so you can see how it works.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the Oracle vs Deno JavaScript trademark case, Oracle has asked &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181157/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;for a two month extension to proceedings&lt;/a&gt;, which &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181099/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Deno has agreed to.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patrick Brosset notes that, as of last month's release of Firefox 147, &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181100/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;you can now use JS modules in service workers&lt;/a&gt; on all major¬†browsers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A cute technical trick for &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181101/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;using the browser's &lt;code&gt;canvas&lt;/code&gt; element to compress textual data from JavaScript.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEASES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181102/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Vuetify 4.0&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Vue framework for building responsive UIs. (&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181103/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Upgrade¬†docs.&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181104/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;npm v11.10.0&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Maintainers can now add/update trusted publishing configs across multiple packages simultaneously. There's also a new &lt;code&gt;--min-release-age&lt;/code&gt;¬†option.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181105/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Node.js v25.7.0 (Current)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181106/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;v24.14.0 (LTS)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181107/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;ESLint 10.0.2&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181109/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Hono 4.12&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181110/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Deno 2.6.10&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181111/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Electron 40.6&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181112/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Three.js r183&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0; padding-right: 0;  padding-left: 0;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üìñ¬† Articles and Videos&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181113/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/w_1280,e_sharpen:60,q_auto/zycphwmqibxis7axptyu.jpg" width="640" style="      line-height: 100%;     "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181113/rss" title="cpojer.net" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;The Fastest Frontend Tooling for Humans and AI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Christoph (of Jest fame) covers his preferred tools for getting your JavaScript tool stack running as fast as possible. It‚Äôs also intended for LLMs to process via &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181114/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;this Markdown¬†version.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Christoph Nakazawa &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181115/rss" title="hacks.mozilla.org" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Goodbye &lt;code&gt;innerHTML&lt;/code&gt;, Hello &lt;code&gt;setHTML&lt;/code&gt; for Stronger XSS Protection&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî As¬†of v148, Firefox &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181116/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;supports&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181117/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Sanitizer API.&lt;/a&gt; Rather than assigning HTML to DOM nodes with &lt;code&gt;innerHTML&lt;/code&gt;, you can use &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181118/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;&lt;code&gt;setHTML&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for safety by default. It‚Äôs a cutting-edge feature, with Chrome 146 (beta) also adding support, but nothing in Safari yet, so &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181119/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;DOMPurify&lt;/a&gt; will remain useful for a¬†while.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Mozilla Hacks &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181120/rss" title="go.clerk.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Clerk's Free Tier Now Covers 50,000 MRUs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Up from 10K. MFA included in Pro. Unlimited apps on all plans. No per-app upgrades¬†anymore.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Clerk &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #993 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181121/rss" title="blog.platformatic.dev" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Halving Node.js Memory Usage with Pointer Compression&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Cloudflare, Igalia, and the Node project have collaborated on &lt;code&gt;node-caged&lt;/code&gt;, a Node.js 25 Docker image with V8 pointer compression enabled, yielding up to 50% memory savings. Matteo digs into all the¬†details.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Matteo Collina &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üì∫ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181122/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;My Angular Stack in 2026&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì An opinionated walk through tools the author would pick if starting a new Angular project¬†now. &lt;cite&gt;Rainer Hahnekamp&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181123/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;How to Publish to npm from GitHub Actions&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Using the new npm OIDC trusted publishing¬†workflow. &lt;cite&gt;Gleb Bahmutov&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181124/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Building an Endless Procedural Snake with Three.js and WebGL&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;cite&gt;Sujen Phea&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0; padding-right: 0;  padding-left: 0;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üõ†¬†Code &amp;amp; Tools&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181125/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/w_1280,e_sharpen:60,q_auto/jjew9kogqu11p8nqfugy.jpg" width="640" style="      line-height: 100%;     "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181125/rss" title="openseadragon.github.io" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;OpenSeadragon 6.0: A Web Viewer for High Resolution Images&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A big step forward for a project that‚Äôs almost 15 years old, and one of few stable, trusty options for rendering ultra-high resolution images for users to zoom into and pan around. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181126/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Version 6&lt;/a&gt; introduces a new async and cache-managed pipeline, making it &lt;em&gt;far&lt;/em&gt; more efficient at¬†scale.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;OpenSeadragon Contributors &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üí° OpenSeadragon was recently used as the basis for the &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181127/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 600;"&gt;Isometric NYC&lt;/a&gt; (well worth reading about in its own right!)¬†project.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181128/rss" title="surveyjs.io" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;SurveyJS: JavaScript Libraries for Dynamic Web Forms&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Build JSON-driven forms in your app (React/Angular/Vue) without SaaS limitations. Keep full ownership of your¬†data.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;SurveyJS &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #993 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/181129/rss" title="mikemcl.github.io" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;bignumber.js 10.0: Library for Arbitrary-Precision Arithmetic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Works around limitations of JavaScript‚Äôs &lt;code&gt;Number&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;BigInt&lt;/code&gt; types, such as if you need to work with very large non-integers. Usefully, the library is included on the page so you can play with it in the JS¬†console.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Michael Mclaughlin &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

